The paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) in robotic science, specifically in manipulation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the generation of human-like behavior and intelligence, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of DRL also involves training neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The manipulation tasks also involve visual perception, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the robot's ability to discern when to continue or give up, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
